1. How often do scuba cylinders need testing in the UK?

Under UK and UKAS guidelines, SCUBA cylinders:

* Periodic Inspection (PI): Every 2.5 years (commonly known as visual inspection)
* Hydrostatic Test (PIAT): Every 5 years (commonly known as hydro inspection)
* ‚Ā†O2 Clean Cylinders: Every 15 months (excluding 100% O2 dedicated cylinders)

All testing is carried out in accordance with IDEST standards and marked accordingly.


